B.T5=new A.hf("When designing, designers have to keep in mind the reality of their work. Is it feasible in the real world? The constants I am applying exist in the real world? And this applies to every aspect of design, whether it is a poster, a magazine, a font, an interface etc. For example, if a design for a t-shirt contains some special colors, textures and thin lines, our budget or the available technology may not be able to make our dreams a reality. That\u2019s why when I design, I always make sure what I am doing can be applied to the final product. As a graphic designer prints a poster multiple times before the final version, a UI/UX designer needs to check that the users can actually use the interface both from a design perspective and a usability check.\n\nBut for some special projects, I take it a bit further. As a hobbyist developer, I choose to develop my own designs and ideas to actual products, like this website, designed and created from scratch.",null,B.aJ,B.k1)
