B.WA=new A.eJ(B.UO,B.TY,B.UP,B.Ve,B.TE,B.TL,B.Ug,B.V6,B.Us,B.VD,B.Te,B.Tv,B.Vz,B.VQ,B.Tn)
B.d4=new A.t(!0,null,null,null,null,null,16,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.WB=new A.bx('Motions graphics presenting the channel\'s program for the "Old" movie in Alpha Greek channel.',null,B.d4,null,null,null,null)
B.WC=new A.bx('The design is based on the widely used motion graphics design for "Upcoming" content on TV channels around the world. I tried to use this approach to the conventional channel program video by adding some more eye-catching visual effects and improving its importance on the screen. What is more, the smooth transitions as well as the position of the graphics catch the attention of the watcher and ensure a readable and familiar experience.',null,B.d4,null,null,null,null)
B.TP=new A.t(!0,null,null,null,null,null,35,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.WD=new A.bx("The approach",null,B.TP,null,null,null,null)
B.WE=new A.bx("The shortcuts were designed by me specifically for this skin. As I could not find an existing icon pack matching the design or including all the necessary icons, I decided to create my own. They are based on the fluent design system of Windows 10 and have a gradient-style approach, creating depth and adding to the skins character.\n\nIn the past, there have been attempts to please them as a separate icon pack but the work demand was very high and the each icon\u2019s adaptability to the new design was not guaranteed. The project as available for some time but was eventually taken down.",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.WG=new A.bx("ERT1 Greek TV channel Blockbuster Series advertisement.",null,B.d4,null,null,null,null)
B.WH=new A.bx("The goal of this feature for the future is to create fully automatic updates that happen automatically when users open their computer. This will make the use experience even more fluent removing the user\u2019s need to check for updates completely. Due to some limitations of rainmeter, progress is slow while I am doing a deeper research about multiple other ways to integrate this feature. Right now, all I can say is \u201ccoming soon\u201d!\n\nAnother possible idea is to create a skin distribution platform (like google play store) where developers can upload their skins and be eligible for OTA updates. There as been a test in the past creatin a platform like tis, but didn't go forward to due to its huge workload and platform limitations tat currently, I don't have the appropriate knowledge to work around.",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.WJ=new A.bx("The font selection was one of the most crucial decision for he skin\u2019s appearance. The type of each font can shape the skin\u2019s character and it is the first asset that users see when selecting a skin to decorate their desktop. Summer loving is one of my favorite handwritten fonts as it has many alternative glyphs for most letters and its texture creates a summer vibe that really suits the skin\u2019s character. Google sans works as the main font. In comparison to summer loving it is rounder, creating a much needed contrast to its pointier edges. Google sans also offers great readability and it\u2019s both great for large text and small paragraphs, useful in the music player and the settings menu.",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.WK=new A.bx("To create automatic updates, first it is needed to store the new files to an online database where they can be downloaded at any time GitHub is an excellent tool that not only stores the new files but also keeps track of version history and can offer the open source flag for any project. Then, after creating a GitHub repository, I made a script using basic PowerShell language which simply fetches (downloads) the repository as a .zip. After that, it unzips the file and replaces the old files with the new ones in the Rainmeter\u2019s skin folder.\n\nThis method is accompanied by an update checker in the settings which checks the current skin\u2019s version by reading a string in a local file and comparing it to another online file which contains the newest version as a string. If those versions match, the skin is up to date but if the local version is smaller than the online one, there is an update available. When pressing the \u201cCheck for updates\u201d button, the algorithm retrieves both strings, removes dots, coverts them to intEgers and makes the comparison with a simple substraction.\n\nThis simple approach was part of a detailed research on Rainmeter\u2019s capabilities and other languages, such as lua which is part of Rainmeter\u2019s development.",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.WL=new A.bx("Ellinikon Vintage and Ellinikon Seaside typically operate independently but occasionally both are open simultaneously. The identity of Ellinikon Vintage is characterized by bold colors, strong typography, and vintage imagery. In contrast, Ellinikon Seaside emphasizes glamour and vibrant colors. Both entities share a common principle: events are communicated with a prominent, logo-like title, followed by additional information presented with lower hierarchy.",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.Tc=new A.t(!0,null,null,null,null,null,30,B.be,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.WM=new A.bx("Got lost in all these projects?",null,B.Tc,B.d3,null,null,null)
B.WN=new A.bx("ClockWorld\u2019s layout is based on familiarity and ease of access. It is made sure that users can find and access information without doubt and misunderstandings. Thus, the screen is split into 4 parts and in each one there is the piece of information that suits best comfortably-wise. First, on top there is the artistic part of he skin which serves as a mental boost providing a happy message to the user. Secondly, starting from the left the music information ensures that readability rules are kept in check as most countries in the world read from left to right. After that, on the right there is the clock which is placed according to the windows original clock, with the goal of embracing familiarity. Last, the shortcuts on the bottom.",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.WP=new A.bx("views",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.WQ=new A.bx("Phase 10 is a universally inclusive card game suitable for families and groups of friends, transcending age boundaries with its engaging gameplay. While appealing to a diverse demographic, the primary player base typically falls w ithin the age range of 12 to 65 years. This demographic exhibits a propensity for critical thinking and strategic organization, attributes integral to success in the game. From a design perspective, this necessitates a user interface and navigation system that seamlessly accommodates players of all ages. Ensuring a universally accessible and enjoyable experience across this broad age spectrum is paramount to the game's design objectives.",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.WR=new A.bx("The logo",null,B.k3,null,null,null,null)
B.WS=new A.bx("favorites",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.WU=new A.bx("badges",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.WW=new A.bx("The settings menu is the best example of a good user experience in every application. In clockworld, it enables the customization of the skin in various ways, split into categories. it manages to display a big amount of information organized in a very convenient way. Just like that, clockworld settings menu features consistency along with sleek and user friendly environment despite rainmeter\u2019s restrictions. By using packages created by the community and with the advice of its people, this interface came to life and it\u2019s praised as one of he best Rainmeter settings menus out there.",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.WX=new A.bx("The skin\u2019s design is based on ClockWorld. As a designer, I want to keep a specific style that characterizes my work and makes it recognizable among other creators. Thus, I chose to keep the most prominent design choices present in ClockWorld and give them  slight twist, making something different from the same successful base. Overall, Sparse\u2019s design is very straightforward with two widgets, one on top the top and another on the bottom of the screen, coming down to information hierarchy and visual balance. The time, date and weather widgets are grouped together transforming that part of he desktop to a status center that displays basic information about everyday things. On the other hand, the music player on the bottom of the screen works as a simple indicator of the current playing song, while giving an artistic style to the desktop. All in all, the skin\u2019s design is focused on keeping things as hassle-free as possible by including the basic information anyone would need during their time using their devices. ",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.WY=new A.bx("Genres presentation for the VH1 music channel. The process follows the previous principle where all the genres are presented on their own with a corresponding music video and at the end, all the genres graphics together presenting the channel's content identity as a whole.",null,B.d4,null,null,null,null)
B.Ts=new A.t(!0,null,null,null,null,null,40,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.WZ=new A.bx("Moving away from the classics",null,B.Ts,null,null,null,null)
B.X_=new A.bx("The basic color palette of ClockWorld comes from the selected wallpapers, each one representing the color of the sunlight at that time of the day. As a highly customizable skin, the colors shouldn\u2019t be tied to one or two specifics but work as  base for user changes. Via the settings menu, the user can select any color or each of the 5 timestamps of the day and create their own version of he skin.",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.X0=new A.bx("The Settings menu is heavily inspired by he windows 10 Fluent design system which was a successful story when it came out. The design is simple and is focused on usability without compromising on design familiarity, creating a user friendly design. The view window is split into two parts, the settings categories and the settings options. Its way of usage is really simple as users are already accustomed with this type of design from their operating system.\n\nFirst, the categories are easily recognizable by the corresponding icon in front of the text for fast reading. The wallpaper color, described before, works as the main (accent) color declaring which category is selected. After navigating to one, users can access the Settings on the right side of the window. There, depending on the type, can users interact with all kinds of interface elements such as buttons, text fields and toggles, Each one of them follows common design rules as follows:\n\nAction buttons: Filled with a light black color with rounded corners. Provide some kind of action when clicked.\nText boxes: Outlined boxes with the accent color as border. Enables clicking for entering information.\nToggles: Colored with the accent color when turned on, outlined with white when turned off.\n\nEvery skin has very similar style of Settings menu. This is done in order to effectively manage adaptability and scalability for the long term. Despite that, every skin has its own special settings and thus the Settings  changes its content but with keeping the overall design parameters the same.",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.X1=new A.bx("ClockWorld was voted as the 8th best Rainmeter skin of 2022. Its minimalistic but fully customizable design provides usability that basic windows devices lack. Features like app shortcuts and music controls enhance the user\u2019s experience while beautiful alternating wallpapers create a new scenery 5 times a day. ",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.X4=new A.bx("The skin\u2019s design is focused on simplicity with some bits of character, like the slight gradient color in the time. It\u2019s focused on being more practical than decorative, with clear information organized in a very distinct way.\n\nMeenimal\u2019s layout is inspired by the mobile design world where the status information is grouped together. Lines divide the information and the size plays the role of hierarchy. The time and date are the most prominent while otherI secondary elements are smaller and grouped together. Finally, a nice touch of a quote that changes every few minutes adds a emotional touch to the skin and creates a pleasant working environment.",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.X5=new A.bx('Influenced by many other successful motion graphic designs for TV channels, I took advantage of the characteristic shape inside "ERT"\'s "R" letter and used it as the primary form. Its appealing effect is caused by smooth opacity and position transitions which describe the overall character and design principles of the channel. The "Inside R" shape is playing a key part and is moving around with the basic information elements as a guide both for the eye and the ierarchy.',null,B.d4,null,null,null,null)
B.X6=new A.bx("Initial approach",null,B.k3,null,null,null,null)
B.X8=new A.bx("Remvi's unique brunch establishment demanded a sophisticated approach to its social media identity. Primarily hosting weekly events and special holiday dinners, Remvi adopts a refined and premium style. The color palette is inspired by the interior decor, emphasizing gold and olive green hues. The design prominently features minimal script typography, ensuring clarity while allowing essential details to stand out. This cohesive aesthetic conveys an overall impression of sleek, high-end service, underscoring the delicacy and elegance that Remvi offers.",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.Xa=new A.bx("Each genre is represented by a different shape and a color, making it recognisable among the others and providing a sense of change while the element alignment stays the same. Interesting text and shape animations, represent the genre's style and keep the viewer's attention.",null,B.d4,null,null,null,null)
B.Xb=new A.bx("Don't worry, you can just return to Home",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.Xd=new A.bx("Integrating the weather widget was one of the biggest coding challenges for this skin, and still remains one. Constant API overloads, wrong web scrapping, server shutdowns and other issues have shaped the lifecycle of this widget. Despite that, design-wise it represents the most basic information anyone could use at any time of the day with the current temperature being the most prominent element. ",null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.Xe=new A.bx("Coming soon",null,B.ys,null,null,null,null)
